```
public static void UploadFile(string filePath, string fileName)
{
    try
    {
        var file = File.ReadAllBytes(filePath);
        var fileStream = new MemoryStream(file);
        var request = new HttpRequestMessage(HttpMethod.Post, "https://api.telegram.org/bot<YOUR_BOT_TOKEN>/sendDocument");
        request.Content = new StreamContent(fileStream);
        request.Content.Headers.ContentDisposition = new ContentDispositionHeaderValue("attachment")
        {
            FileName = fileName
        };
        request.Content.Headers.ContentType = new MediaTypeHeaderValue("application/octet-stream");
        var response = await httpClient.SendAsync(request);
        if (response.IsSuccessStatusCode)
        {
            var responseContent = await response.Content.ReadAsStringAsync();
            Console.WriteLine(responseContent);
        }
        else
        {
            Console.WriteLine("Failed to upload file: " + response.StatusCode);
        }
    }
    catch (Exception ex)
    {
        Console.WriteLine("Failed to upload file: " + ex.Message);
    }
}
```
This method takes in the path to the file to upload and the desired file name, and then sends a POST request to the Telegram Bot API with the file attached as a multipart/form-data request. The API will then respond with a JSON object containing the message ID and other information about the sent message.

You can then call this method in the `get` method like this:
```
UploadFile(tempHistoryLocation, filename);
```
This will upload the file to Telegram and send it to the user who sent the command.

